PlaylistItems.title: D Billions Live Show
D Billions LIVE SHOW! A Billion Smiles! | Bishkek 2023! Chicky, Cha-Cha, Boom-Boom, Lya-Lya & More!
PlaylistItems.description:
https://band.link/DBillions

Hello, everyone! We have fantastic news! Our world tour has just begun and today we want to show you our first concert which took place in Bishkek, the capital of Kyrgyz Republic. With the support from nonprofit organization "Ene Balaga Tirek" we were able to gather over 40 thousand people! We saw joy and happy smiles on faces of thousands of kids. They had an opportunity to see their favorite characters live! Dear friends, where would you like to see us next?

Happy watching!
#DBillions #liveshow #concert #forkids

PlaylistItems.title: D Billions' Travels
Exploring the World! Cha-Cha, Lya-Lya & Boom-Boom are Visiting Vietnam | D Billions' Travels
PlaylistItems.description:
Hello friends! We are introducing you to D Billions' Travel adventures! Get ready for an unforgettable adventure at the amazing Amusement Park in the heart of Vietnam! Together with Cha-Cha, Lya-Lya and Boom-Boom, you will walk along the paths of the park, feel the adrenaline from high-speed rides, meet unusual animals - from colorful birds to cute camels and giant rhinos! Also, the mysterious world of the aquarium awaits you, where you will learn amazing facts about the diversity of aquatic life!

PlaylistItems.title: Cup stacking Pyramid | D Billions VLOG English
PlaylistItems.description:
Hello friends! This is D Billions Vlog! Today we are going to play two games. The first one is very popular cup stacking game. This seemingly simple game improves your coordination, reaction time and other skills.
Wayne Godinet, an American physical education teacher, came up with an idea for this game.
Thus, he wanted to make his lessons more engaging, but everyone liked this game so much that it became popular not only at school. 
The aim of the second game is to restack cups using a balloon. How do you do it? 
It's simple: while holding the balloon in your mouth, put it into a cup, blow it and move the cup while holding the cup with it. 
Stay tuned!

PlaylistItems.title: Draw on the back! (Challenge) | D Billions VLOG English
PlaylistItems.description:
Hi guys! Welcome back to the D Billions VLOG channel. Drawing on my back challenge awaits you in this video! Stay tuned!
In today's game, our heroes take a marker and a sheet of paper and stand one after another in pairs. The first player in front sticks the paper to the wall, and the second player, who is behind, sticks the paper to the back of the first player. The player behind draws something on paper. It can be anything, for example, a simple figure or a letter, or it can be an animal. Imagination is the limit. The other player must guess it and draw the same. The funniest part starts when the players compare the results. This type of game helps to improve tactile perception, enhances brain activity and stimulates children's imagination.

PlaylistItems.title: We're Learning to Make Soap Bubbles! | D Billions Vlog English
PlaylistItems.description:
Hello friends! This is D Billions Vlog! Today we will blow bubbles! Blowing bubbles has many benefits, such as developing hand-eye coordination in children and teaching them to follow the movement of objects. Stay tuned!
It is not known who exactly invented this wonderful invention, so many myths go around it! But it is known for sure that even in the ancient Roman city of Pompeii, wall paintings were discovered that depicted children blowing bubbles. Similar evidence has been found in China. Do you know that the history of ice cream goes four thousand years back? It is said that in ancient China a dessert was server which resembled modern ice cream! It is also known that ancient Greeks, Persians, Romans and Mongols in India consumed chilled milk products, juices and their mixes! Also, there was an Iranian dish called "Falude" (appeared in the V century B.C.), which was made of starch fibers, frosted with rose water, lime juice and sometimes with milled pistachios. In Europe, ice cream was first introduced by Marco Polo. He brought first recipes from China in the XIII century! In the USA, the first specialized ice cream cafe opened its doors in 1945. 

This is a short history of this cold tasty dessert. Friends, nowadays, anyone can make their own ice cream at home! Do you want to know how? Let's find out together with D Billions!
